Mom, I'm a prisoner, but don't cry
 Darned, now like new.
 I was treated by a Donetsk doctor
 U has become, strict and severe.
 Treated me.  Do you hear mom?
 I hit the city from "Gradov",
 And half the hospital is just in the trash,
 But he treated me: "So it is necessary."
 Mom, I'm a monster, I'm sorry.
 In the streams of lies we got lost.
 All my life I have to bear this cross.
 Now my eyes are open.
 We were taken to places
 Where did the shells go?
 And we did not believe our eyes:
 What have we done with the Donbass!
 The hospitals are full of wounded.
 Here every Kyiv curses.
 Father, whiter than a sheet,
 The dead child shakes.
 Mother, I am a monster, an executioner.
 And there are no terrorists here, mother.
 Here only the groan of the human and
 cry,
 And we are scarier for them
 fascists.
 We, mothers, were sent to slaughter,
 The battalion commander did not feel sorry for us.
 The militiaman shouted to me: "Stop!
 GET DOWN, you brat!", and so on.
 obscenity.
 He didn't want to shoot me.
 He is a Human and I am a killer.
 Taken out of battle!  Do you hear, mother,
 Me, Donbas bloodsucker!
 Mom, I'm a prisoner, but don't cry.
 Darned, now like new.
 I was treated by a Donetsk doctor
 Tired, strict and harsh.
 He did medical duty
 And I, burning with shame,
 For the first time I could think:
 Who needs a war like this?
 Sergey Gusev

We adjust the fire of the Ukrainian artillery, being where the technical support decides how many meters of Ukrainian land will be cleared of the occupiers. The other day we received a new DJI Matrice 300 drone. Many thanks to everyone involved! This drone has more tactical capabilities than the DJI Matrice 30 that our unit already has.
